<subSubSection pageId="108" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="108.[151,1436,421,554]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,421,446]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Note.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[271,369,421,446]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[405,531,421,446]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadne" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solitaria">
<emphasis box="[405,531,421,446]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">A. solitaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was examined and, confirming the information presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beatty, J. A." box="[1218,1432,422,446]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" pagination="433 - 518" part="139" refId="ref87290" refString="Beatty, J. A. (1970) The spider genus Ariadna in the Americas (Araneae, Dysderidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 139 (8), 433 - 518." title="The spider genus Ariadna in the Americas (Araneae, Dysderidae)" type="journal article" year="1970">Beatty (1970: 482)</bibRefCitation>
, it is an immature specimen. This is the only known specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[876,968,457,482]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[876,968,457,482]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Ariadna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in this locality, and although its resemblance with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1926" box="[360,473,493,518]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arthuri">
<emphasis box="[360,473,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">A. arthuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the macrosetae pattern of the legs I‒II is different. Until other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[1218,1310,493,518]" class="Arachnida" family="Segestriidae" genus="Ariadna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="108" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1310,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Ariadna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[253,301,530,554]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">type</typeStatus>
locality could be collected, we here decide to position this species as 
<emphasis box="[1084,1256,529,554]" italics="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">nomem dubium</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
